quran[178]{c,v,t}:
  29,46,"And do not wrangle with the people of the Book, except for what is better; save with those who have been unjust amongst them and who say, 'We believe in what is sent down to us, And what has been sent down to you; our God and your God is one, and we are unto Him resigned"
  29,47,Thus did we send down to thee the Book; and every one to whom we have given the Book believes therein. But these will not believe therein; though none gainsay our signs except the misbelievers
  29,48,"Thou couldst not recite before this any book, nor write it with thy right hand, for in that case those who deem it vain would have doubted"
  29,49,"Nay, but it is evident signs in the breasts of those who are endued with knowledge, and none but the unjust would gainsay our signs"
  29,50,"They say, 'Unless there be sent down upon him signs from his Lord -;' say, 'Verily, signs are with God, and, verily, I am an obvious warner"
  29,51,"Is it not enough for them that we have sent down to thee the Book which thou dost recite to them? verily, in that is a mercy and a reminder to a people who believe"
  29,52,"Say, 'God is witness enough between me and you; He knows what is in the heavens and what is in the earth; and those who believe in falsehood and misbelieve in God, they shall be the losers"
  29,53,"They will wish thee to hasten on the torment; but were it not for a stated and appointed time, the torment would have come upon them suddenly, while yet they did not perceive"
  29,54,"They will wish thee to hurry on the torment, but, verily, hell encompasses the misbelievers"
  29,55,"On the day when the torment shall cover them from above them and from beneath their feet, and He shall say, 'Taste that which ye have done"
  29,56,"O my servants who believe! verily, my land is spacious enough; me therefore do ye worship"
  29,57,"Every soul must taste of death, then unto us shall ye return"
  29,58,"and those who believe and act aright, we will surely inform them of upper chambers in Paradise, beneath which rivers flow; to dwell therein for aye - pleasant is the hire of those who work"
  29,59,those who are patient and rely upon their Lord
  29,60,How many a beast cannot carry its own provision! God provides for it and for you; He both hears and knows
  29,61,"And if thou shouldst ask them, 'Who created the heavens and the earth, and subjected the sun and the moon?' they will surely say, 'God!' how then can they lie"
  29,62,"God extends provision to whomsoever He will of His servants, or doles it out to him; verily, God all things doth know"
  29,63,"And if thou shouldst ask them, 'Who sends down from the heavens water and quickens therewith the earth in its death?' they will surely say, 'God!' say, 'And praise be to God!' nay, most of them have no sense"
  29,64,"This life of the world is nothing but a sport and a play; but, verily, the abode of the next world, that is life,- if they did but know"
  29,65,"And when they ride in the ship they call upon God, making their religion seem sincere to Him; but when He saves them to the shore, behold, they associate others with Him"
  29,66,"that they may disbelieve in our signs; and that they may have some enjoyment: but soon they shall know"
  29,67,"Have they not seen that we have made a safe sanctuary whilst people are being snatched away around them? is it then in falsehood that they will believe, and for the favours of God be ungrateful"
  29,68,"But who is more unjust than he who devises against God a lie, or calls the truth a lie when it comes to him? Is there not in hell a resort for the misbelievers"
  29,69,"but those who fight strenuously for us we will surely guide them into our way, for, verily, God is with those who do well"
  30,1,Missing
  30,2,The Greeks are overcome
  30,3,in the nighest parts of the land; but after being overcome they shall overcome
  30,4,in a few years; to God belongs the order before and after; and on that day the believers shall rejoice
  30,5,"in the help of God;- God helps whom He will, and He is mighty, merciful"
  30,6,"God's promise!- God breaks not His promise, but most men do not know"
  30,7,"They know the outside of this world's life, but of the hereafter they are heedless"
  30,8,"Have they not reflected in themselves, that God created not the heavens and the earth, and what is between the two except in truth, and for a stated and appointed time? but, verily, many men in the meeting of their Lord do disbelieve"
  30,9,"Have they not journeyed on in the land and seen how was the end of those before them who were stronger than they, and who turned up the ground and cultivated it more than they do cultivate it? and there came to them their apostles with manifest signs; for God would never wrong them: it was themselves they wronged"
  30,10,"Then evil was the end of those who did evil, in that they said the signs of God were lies and mocked thereat"
  30,11,"God produces a creation, then He makes it go back again, then unto Him shall ye return"
  30,12,"And on the day when the Hour shall rise, the sinners shall be confused"
  30,13,and they shall not have amongst their partners intercessors; and their partners shall they deny
  30,14,"And on the day when the Hour shall rise, on that day shall they be scattered apart"
  30,15,"and as for those who believe and do right, they in the garden shall be joyful"
  30,16,"and as for those who misbelieved and said our signs and the meeting of the hereafter were lies, they shall be in the torment arraigned"
  30,17,"Celebrated be the praises of God, when ye are in the evening and when ye are in the morning"
  30,18,"for to Him belongs praise in the heavens and the earth! and at the evening, and when ye are at noon"
  30,19,"He brings forth the living from the dead, and brings forth the dead from the living; and He quickens the earth after its death, and thus shall ye too be brought forth"
  30,20,"And of His signs is this, that He hath created you from dust; then, behold, ye are mortals who are spread abroad"
  30,21,"And of His signs is this, that He hath created for you of yourselves wives with whom ye may cohabit; He has made between you affection and pity. Verily, in that are signs unto a people who reflect"
  30,22,"And of His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the diversity of your tongues and colours; verily, in that are signs unto the worlds"
  30,23,"And of His signs is your sleep by night and by day; and your craving after His grace. Verily, in that are signs unto a people who do hear"
  30,24,"And of His signs is this, that He shows you lightning for fear and hope; and sends down from the sky water, and quickens therewith the earth after its death; verily, in that are signs unto a people who have sense"
  30,25,"And of His signs is this, that the heavens and the earth stand by His order; then when He calls you from the earth, lo! ye shall come forth"
  30,26,"His are those who are in the heavens and the earth, and all to Him are devoted"
  30,27,"And He it is who produces a creation and then makes it to go back again; for it is very easy to Him; and His are the loftiest similitudes in the heavens and the earth; and He is the mighty, wise"
  30,28,"He has struck out for you a parable from yourselves; have ye of what your right hand possess partners in what we have bestowed upon you, so that ye share alike therein? do ye fear them as ye fear each other?- Thus do we detail the signs unto a people who have sense"
  30,29,"Nay, when those who are unjust follow their lusts without knowledge,- and who shall guide him whom God has led astray? and they shall have none to help"
  30,30,"Set thy face steadfast towards the religion as an 'Hanif, according to the constitution whereon God has constituted men; there is no altering the creation of God, that is the standard religion, though most men do not know"
  30,31,"Turn repentant towards Him; and fear Him, and be steadfast in prayer; and be not of the idolaters"
  30,32,"Of those who have divided their religion and become sects, every party in what they have, rejoice"
  30,33,"And when distress touches men they call upon their Lord, repentant towards Him; then when He has made them taste mercy from Himself, behold! a party of them associate others with their Lord"
  30,34,that they may disbelieve in what we have brought them;- but enjoy yourselves; for hereafter ye shall know
  30,35,Or have we sent down to them authority which speaks of what they do associate with Him
  30,36,"And when we have made men taste of mercy, they rejoice therein; and if there befall them evil for what their hands have sent before, behold! they are in despair"
  30,37,"Have they not seen that God extends provision to whom He pleases, or doles it out? verily, in that are signs unto a people who believe"
  30,38,"Then give to the kinsman his due, and to the poor and to the wayfarer; that is better for those who desire the face of God, and these it is who are prosperous"
  30,39,"And what ye put out to usury that it may increase with the wealth of men, it shall not increase with God; but what ye put out in alms, desiring the face of God - these it is who shall gain double"
  30,40,"It is God who created you and then provided for you; and then will make you die, and then will quicken you again; is there any of your partners who can do aught of that? Celebrated be His praises, and exalted be He above what they associate with Him"
  30,41,"Trouble hath appeared in the land and the sea, for what men's hands have gained! to make them taste a part of that which they have done,- haply they may return"
  30,42,"Say, 'Journey on in the land, and behold what was the end of those before you,- most of them were idolaters"
  30,43,"Set thy face steadfast to the standard religion, before there come a day from God which there is no averting; on that day shall they be parted into two bands"
  30,44,"He who misbelieves, upon him is his misbelief; but whoso does right, for themselves they are spreading couches"
  30,45,"That He may reward those who believe and do right of His grace; verily, He loves not the misbelievers"
  30,46,"And of His signs is this, that He sends forth the winds with glad tidings, to make you taste of His mercy, and to make the ships go on at His bidding, and that ye may crave of His grace, and haply ye may give thanks"
  30,47,"We have sent before thee apostles unto their people, and they came to them with manifest signs: and we took vengeance upon those who sinned, but due from us it was to help the believers"
  30,48,"God it is who sends forth the winds to stir up clouds; then He spreads them forth over the sky as he pleases; and He breaks them up and ye see the rain come forth from amongst them; and when He causes it to fall upon whom He pleases of His servants, behold they hail it with joy"
  30,49,although before it was sent down upon them they were before then confused
  30,50,"Look then to the vestiges of God's mercy, how He quickens the earth after its death; verily, that is the quickener of the dead, and He is mighty over all"
  30,51,"But if we should send a wind and they should see it yellow, they would after that become misbelievers"
  30,52,"But, verily, thou canst not make the dead to hear, nor canst thou make the deaf to hear the call, when they turn their backs and flee"
  30,53,nor hast thou to guide the blind out of their error; thou canst only make those to hear who believe in our signs and who are resigned
  30,54,"God it is who created you of weakness, then made for you after weakness strength; then made for you after strength, weakness and grey hairs: He creates what He pleases, for He is the knowing, the powerful"
  30,55,"And on the day when the Hour shall rise, the sinners shall swear that they have not tarried save an hour; thus were they wont to lie"
  30,56,"But those who are given knowledge and faith will say, 'We have tarried according to the Book of God, until the day of resurrection;' and this is the day of resurrection, but ye - ye do not know"
  30,57,And on that day their excuse shall profit not those who did wrong; nor shall they be asked to please God again
  30,58,"We have struck out to men in this Qur'an every kind of parable; but if thou shouldst bring them a sign then those who misbelieve will surely say, 'Ye are but followers of vanity"
  30,59,thus does God set a stamp upon the hearts of those who do not know
  30,60,"Be thou patient then; verily, God's promise is true! and let them not flurry thee who are not sure"
  31,1,M
  31,2,These are the signs of the wise Book
  31,3,a guidance and a mercy to those who do well
  31,4,who are steadfast in prayer and give alms and who of the hereafter are sure
  31,5,"these are in Guidance from their Lord, and these are the prosperous"
  31,6,"And amongst men is one who buys sportive legends, to lead astray from God's path, without knowledge, and to make a jest of it; these, for them is shameful woe"
  31,7,"And when our signs are recited to him, he turns his back, too big with pride, as though he heard them not, - as if in his two ears were dullness. But give to him glad tidings of grievous woe"
  31,8,"Verily, those who believe and do right, for them are gardens of pleasure"
  31,9,"to dwell therein for aye;- God's promise in truth, and He is mighty, wise"
  31,10,"He created the heavens without pillars that ye can see, and He threw upon the earth firm mountains lest it should move with you; and He dispersed thereon every sort of beast; and we send down from the heavens water, and we caused to grow therein of every noble kind"
  31,11,"This is God's creation; show me what others beside Him have created; - nay, the unjust are in obvious error"
  31,12,"We did give unto Loqman wisdom, saying, 'Thank God; for he who thanks God is only thankful for his own soul; and he who is ungrateful - verily, God is independent, worthy of praise"
  31,13,"And when Loqman said to his son while admonishing him, 'O my boy! associate none with God, for, verily, such association is a mighty wrong"
  31,14,For we have commended his parents to man; his mother bore him with weakness upon weakness; and his weaning is in two years; - 'Be thankful to me and to thy parents; for unto me shall your journey be
  31,15,"But if they strive with thee that thou shouldst associate with me that which thou hast no knowledge of, then obey them not. But associate with them in the world with kindness, and follow the way of him who repentant unto me; then unto me is your return, and I will inform you of that which ye have done"
  31,16,"O my son! verily, if there were the weight of a grain of mustard seed and it were (hidden) in the rock, or in the heaven, or in the earth, God would bring it (to light). Verily, God is subtle, well aware"
  31,17,"O my son! be steadfast in prayer, and bid what is reasonable and forbid what is wrong; be patient of what befalls thee, verily, that is one of the determined affairs"
  31,18,"And twist not thy cheek proudly, nor walk in the land haughtily; verily, God loves not every arrogant boaster"
  31,19,"but be moderate in thy walk, and lower thy voice; verily, the most disagreeable of voices is the voice of asses"
  31,20,"Have ye not seen that God has subjected to you what is in the heavens and what is in the earth, and has poured down upon you His favours, outwardly and inwardly? but amongst men are those who wrangle about God, without knowledge, and without guidance, and without an illuminating book"
  31,21,"And when it is said to them, 'Follow what God has sent down;' they say, 'Nay! we will follow what we found our fathers agreed upon;' - what! though Satan calls them to the torment of the blaze"
  31,22,"But he who resigns his face unto God, and does good, he has grasped the firm handle; unto God is the issue of affairs"
  31,23,"But he who misbelieves, let not his misbelief grieve thee; to us is their return, and we will inform them of what they do; - for, verily, God knows the nature of men's breasts"
  31,24,We will let them enjoy themselves a little; then we will force them to rigorous woe
  31,25,"And if thou shouldst ask them who created the heavens and the earth, they will surely say, 'God.' Say, 'Praise be to God!' but most of them do not know"
  31,26,"God's is what is in the heavens and what is in the earth; verily, God, He is the independent, worthy of praise"
  31,27,"And were the trees that are in the earth pens, and the sea (ink) with seven more seas to swell its tide, the words of God would not be spent; verily, God is mighty, wise"
  31,28,"Your creation and your rising again are but as that of one soul; verily, God both hears and sees"
  31,29,"Dost thou not see that God joins on the night to the day, and joins on the day to the night, and has subjected the sun and the moon, - each of them runs on unto an appointed time? and that God of what ye do is well aware"
  31,30,"That is because God, He is true, and because what ye call on beside Him is falsehood, and because God, He is the high, the great"
  31,31,"Dost thou not see that the ship rides on in the sea by the favour of God, that He may show you of His signs? verily, in that are signs to every grateful person"
  31,32,"And when a wave like shadows covers them, they call on God, being sincere in their religion; and when He saves them to the shore, then amongst them are some who halt between two opinions. But none gainsays our signs save every perfidious misbeliever"
  31,33,"O ye folk! fear your Lord and dread the day when the father shall not atone for his son, nor shall the child atone aught for its parent. Verily, the promise of God is true! Say, 'Let not the life of this world beguile you; and let not the beguiler beguile you concerning God"
  31,34,"Verily, God, with Him is the knowledge of the Hour; and He sends down the rain; and He knows what is in the wombs; and no soul knows what it is that it shall earn to-morrow; and no soul knows in what land it shall die; verily, God is knowing, well aware"
  32,1,M
  32,2,"The revelation of the Book, there is no doubt therein, from the Lord of the worlds"
  32,3,"Do they say, 'He has forged it?' Nay! it is the truth from thy Lord, that thou mayest warn a people, to whom no warner has come before thee, haply they may be guided"
  32,4,God it is who created the heavens and the earth and what is between the two in six days; then He made for the throne! ye have no patron beside Him and no intercessor; are ye not then mindful
  32,5,"He governs the affair from the heaven unto the earth; then shall it ascend to him in a day, the measure of which is as a thousand years of what ye number"
  32,6,"That is He who knows the unseen and the visible; the mighty, the merciful"
  32,7,"who has made the best of the creation of everything, and produced the creation of man from clay"
  32,8,then He made his stock from an extract of despicable water
  32,9,"then He fashioned him and breathed into him of His spirit, and made for you hearing and eyesight and hearts;- little is it that ye give thanks"
  32,10,"And they say, 'When we are lost in the earth, shall we then become a new creation?' Nay! in the meeting of their Lord they disbelieve"
  32,11,"Say, 'The angel of death shall take you away, he who is given charge of you; then unto your Lord shall ye be returned"
  32,12,"And couldst thou see when the sinners hang down their heads before their Lord, 'O Lord! we have seen and we have heard; send us back then and we will do right. Verily, we are sure"
  32,13,Had we pleased we would have given to everything its guidance; but the sentence was due from me;-I will surely fill hell with the ginns and with men all together
  32,14,"So taste ye, for that ye forgat the meeting of this day of yours,- verily, we have forgotten you! and taste ye the torment of eternity for that which ye have done"
  32,15,"They only believe in our signs who when they are reminded of them fall down adoring and celebrate the praises of their Lord, and are not too big with pride"
  32,16,"As their sides forsake their beds, they call upon their Lord with fear and hope; and of what we have bestowed upon them do they give alms"
  32,17,"No soul knows what is reserved for them of cheerfulness for eye, as a reward for that which they have done"
  32,18,Is he who is a believer like him who is a sinner? they shall not be held equal
  32,19,"As for those who believe and do right, for them are the gardens of resort, an entertainment for that which they have done"
  32,20,"But as for those who commit abomination their resort is the Fire. Every time that they desire to go forth therefrom, we will send them back therein, and it will be said to them, 'Taste ye the torment of the fire which ye did call a lie"
  32,21,"and we will surely make them taste of the torment of the nearer torment beside the greater torment, - haply they may yet return"
  32,22,"Who is more unjust than he who is reminded of the signs of his Lord, and then turns away from them? Verily, we will take vengeance on the sinners"
  32,23,And we did give Moses the Book; be not then in doubt concerning the meeting with him; and we made it a guidance to the children of Israel
  32,24,"And we made amongst them high priests who guided by our bidding, since they were patient and were sure of our signs"
  32,25,"Verily, thy Lord, he shall decide between them on the resurrection day concerning that whereon they do dispute"
  32,26,"Is it not conspicuous to them how many generations we have destroyed before them? they walk over their dwellings! verily, in that are signs: do they not then hear"
  32,27,"Have they not seen that we drive the water to the sterile land, and bring forth thereby corn from which their cattle and themselves do eat? do they not then see"
  32,28,"And they say, 'When shall this decision come if ye do tell the truth"
  32,29,"Say, 'On the day of the decision their faith shall not profit those who misbelieved, nor shall they be respited"
  32,30,"turn then from them and wait; verily, they are waiting too"
  33,1,"O thou prophet! fear God and obey not the misbelievers and hypocrites; verily, God is ever knowing, wise"
  33,2,"But follow what thou art inspired with from thy Lord; verily, God of what you do is ever well aware"
  33,3,"And rely upon God, for God is guardian enough"
  33,4,"God has not made for any man two hearts in his inside; nor has He made your wives,- whom you back away from,- your real mothers; nor has He made your adopted sons your real sons. That is what ye speak with your mouths; but God speaks the truth and He guides to the path"
  33,5,"Call them by their fathers' names; that is more just in God's sight; but if ye know not their fathers, then they are your brothers in religion and your clients. There is no crime against you for what mistakes ye make therein; but what your hearts do purposely - but God is ever forgiving and merciful"
  33,6,"The prophet is nearer of kin to the believers than themselves, and his wives are their mothers. And blood relations are nearer in kin to each other by the Book of God than the believers and those who fled; only your doing kindness to your kindred, that is traced in the Book"
  33,7,"And when we took of the prophets their compact, from thee and from Noah, and Abraham, and Moses, and Jesus the son of Mary, and took of them a rigid compact"
  33,8,that He might ask the truth-tellers of their truth. But He has prepared for those who misbelieve a grievous woe
  33,9,O ye who believe! remember God's favours towards you when hosts came to you and we sent against them a wind and hosts that ye could not see;- and God knew what ye were doing
  33,10,"When they came upon you from above you and from below you, and when your eyesights were distracted and your hearts came up into your throats, and ye suspected God with certain suspicions"
  33,11,There were the believers tried and were made to quake with a severe quaking
  33,12,"And when the hypocrites and those in whose hearts was sickness said, 'God and His Apostle have only promised us deceitfully"
  33,13,"And when a party of them said, 'O people of Yathreb; there is no place for you (here), return then (to the city).' And a part of them asked leave of the prophet (to return), saying, 'Verily, our houses are defenceless;' but they were not defenceless, they only wished for flight"
  33,14,But had they been entered upon from its environs and then been asked to show treason they would have done so; but they would only have tarried there a little while
  33,15,"They had covenanted with God before, that they would not turn their backs; and God's covenant shall be enquired of"
  33,16,"Say, 'Flight shall avail you naught; if ye fly from death or slaughter, even then ye shall be granted enjoyment only for a little"
  33,17,"Say, 'Who is it that can save you from God, if He wish you evil, or wish you mercy?' but they will not find beside God a patron or a helper"
  33,18,"Say, 'God knows the hinderers amongst you, and those who say to their brethren, \"Come along unto us,\" and show but little valour"
  33,19,"covetous towards you.' When fear comes thou wilt see them looking towards thee, their eyes rolling like one fainting with death; but when the fear has passed away they will assail you with sharp tongues, covetous of the best. These have never believed, and God will make vain their works, for that is easy with God"
  33,20,"They reckoned that the confederates would never go away; and if the confederates should come they would fain be in the desert with the Arabs, asking for news of you! and if they were amongst you they would fight but little"
  33,21,"Ye had in the Apostle of God a good example for him who hopes for God and the last day, and who remembers God much"
  33,22,"And when the believers saw the confederates they said, 'This is what God and His Apostle promised us; God and His Apostle are true!' and it only increased them in faith and resignation"
  33,23,"Amongst the believers are men who have been true to their covenant with God, and there are some who have fulfilled their vow, and some who wait and have not changed with fickleness"
  33,24,"That God might reward the truthful for their truth, and punish the hypocrites if He please, or turn again towards them;- verily, God is forgiving, merciful"
  33,25,"And God drove back the misbelievers in their rage; they gat no advantage;- God was enough for the believers in the fight, for God is strong, mighty"
  33,26,And He drove down those of the people of the Book who had helped them from their fortresses and hurled dread into their hearts; a part ye slew and ye took captive a part
  33,27,"and He gave you their land, and their dwellings, and their property for an inheritance, and a land ye had not trodden, for God is ever mighty over all"
  33,28,"O thou prophet! say to thy wives, 'If ye be desirous of the life of this world and its adornments, come, I will give you them to enjoy and I will let you range handsomely at large"
  33,29,"But if ye be desirous of God and His Apostle and of the abode of the hereafter, verily, God has prepared for those of you who do good a mighty hire"
  33,30,"O ye women of the prophet! whosoever of you commits manifest fornication, doubled shall be her torment twice; and that is easy unto God"